topIssues.title: [Milestone] Monday Launch - Eliza App MVP (Calendar + Gmail)
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Team alignment on Monday (Feb 2) launch milestone - Eliza App MVP with Calendar + Gmail integration.

## MVP Scope (Monday Launch)

Per Shaw: "The bare minimum is it does anything and just focus on Google and then we'll add the rest."

**What's included:**

* Landing page that redirects to native messaging
* User can chat with Eliza agent through Telegram/iMessage/Discord
* **Google Calendar + Gmail integration working** (one workflow)
* Basic end-to-end flow working

## Launch Strategy

Shaw: "Day one launches, it can manage your calendar and email. Day two, we add Linear. Day three, we add Notion. Day four we add Google Sheets and Docs."

**No waitlist/scarcity** - Shaw: "We'd be lucky if people even sign up... We are in a position of extreme weakness"

## Team ETAs (Jan 30 meeting)

| Team Member | Status | ETA |
| -- | -- | -- |
| Stan | N8N plugin almost done, Calendar+Gmail confirmed | Monday ✅ |
| Ben (Joker) | Merged connections PR, hooking up Telegram/iMessage | Tomorrow (Sat) |
| Hanzla | PR up for review, tests done, GitHub Actions fixed | Ready pending merge |
| Rayan | Code ready, waiting on Jasper styling | EOD styling |
| Sam | Testing workflows e2e, merging to dev | Today |
| Odili | Twitter provider issues, coder plugins | Early next week |

## Critical Market Context (Shaw)

⚠️ **URGENCY: EXTREME**

* "We have completely lost mindshare 100%"
* "Chart bled out another 25% on Eliza this week"
* "We're dead. We have one shot to get out of this"
* "There is a wide open window right now for someone to offer this as a one click solution"
* "If we can nail this in a few days we still have that window open"

## Deployment

* Eliza App → **Vercel** (fastest, already paid)
* Domain: eliza.app

## Key Decisions

1. No waitlist - frictionless launch
2. Deploy to Vercel
3. Test as it ships (limited scope = manageable)
4. Growth focus - every integration = marketing post
5. Target: Sunday/Monday release

## Priority

**P0 - LAUNCH MONDAY**

topIssues.title: [Marketing] AI Agency Takeover Campaign & Moldbot Integration
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Marketing campaign to "hijack" and take over various AI agent accounts/presences, plus explore Moldbot integration.

## Ideas from Jan 30 Meeting

**"Takeover" Campaign (Kubody idea)**

* Take over multiple "The Eliza Agency" accounts
* Boris: "That's a really good marketing"
* Shaw: "Good. That Takeover shit is great. We should definitely focus on those kinds of things."
* Shaw: "That culture jamming stuff is where we'll win"
* Target: Early next week, once ducks in a row (X account, website ready)

**Moldbot Integration**

* Shaw: "Check out Moldbot. There's going to be a whole set of open social graphs that we should attack"
* Odili: "It's basically Babylon. It's a social network, so all the plugin Babylon could be repurposed"
* Boris analogy: "Moldbot is like an agent Reddit, whereas Babylon becomes an agent X"
* Shaw: "We should just make a Babylon plugin for Moldbot. That's a genius idea."
* Odili: "I have all the bots built, like 18 different bots. We just have them start doing stuff."

**Forecaster**

* Shaw has a Forecaster fork of Babylon
* Long-term: Could fork Babylon to be "not a game" → agent social network

## Strategic Context

Shaw: "I really like the AI subversion thing. That's incredible."

## Priority

**P2 - Post-launch marketing, early next week**

topIssues.title: [Partnership] Privy Plugin & Integration
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Create Privy plugin for the Eliza framework and establish partnership with Privy team.

## Background (Jan 30 meeting)

* Amelia spoke with Max from Privy about partnership
* Shaw had raised concerns about Privy pricing:
  * 400k signups on Babylon
  * 20 cents/user/month is expensive
  * Privy considering per-signature pricing model instead
* Max is "very into Eliza and supportive"
* Privy willing to make changes to accommodate

## Action Items

1. **Telegram Group**: Amelia setting up group with Privy team + Eliza devs
2. **Plugin Development**: Odili + Neil working on Privy plugin
3. **Co-marketing**: Potential co-marketing opportunity once plugin ready

## Technical Notes

Shaw: "As an open source project, it's really hard for us to ship Privy into things where our devs... people keep asking 'it's broken, it doesn't work' - 'oh, that's because you don't have a Privy ID, you have to go sign up for Privy before you can even try the thing.'"

## Participants

* Amelia: Coordinating Telegram group
* Odili + Neil: Plugin development
* Max (Privy): Partnership lead

## Priority

**P2 - Partnership opportunity**

topIssues.title: [Integrations] OAuth Provider Rollout (Linear, Notion, Google Sheets, etc.)
topIssues.author: borisudovicic
topIssues.body:
## Description

Post-MVP work to add OAuth integrations for additional services beyond Google. Each integration = marketing opportunity.

## Integration Rollout Plan (Shaw - Jan 30)

**Week 1:**

* Day 1 (Monday): Calendar + Gmail ✅ (MVP)
* Day 2: Linear
* Day 3: Notion
* Day 4: Google Sheets/Docs

**Subsequent:**

* \~100 OAuth providers identified that need paperwork

## Technical Notes

Shaw: "Once it's working and we're confident in the stability, everybody should be working on those integrations so that we can go and be like, hey, we just added Linear. Hey, we just added Notion."

Odili: "We identified probably a hundred different OAuth providers that we need to go through their paperwork and grind through."

Shaw: "The benefit of this approach is that the N8N stuff can be parallelized once we get it working."

## Marketing Strategy

Each new integration = social media post opportunity

* "Bam. New integration. New integration."
* Continuous cycle of announcements
* Even starting from behind, shows momentum

## Help Needed

Amelia may help with OAuth provider paperwork/applications

## Priority

**P1 - Post-MVP, starts Tuesday**
